This is Perl module String::Slack.

INSTALLATION

String::Slack installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % git clone https://Likk@github.com/Likk/String-Slack.git ./

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

String::Slack documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc String::Slack

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

